      "description": "Make the Coconut Dal batch recipe."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 220°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip the cherry tomatoes onto a tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast for 10–15 mins until soft, jammy and starting to burst."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pick the coriander leaves and finely slice the stems."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip the dal into a saucepan and stir through the coriander stems. Warm over a medium heat until piping hot, loosening with a splash of water if it’s thickened in the fridge."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pop the naan into the oven for the final 2 mins of the tomato roasting time to warm through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spoon the dal into bowls, then top with the roast tomatoes, spoonfuls of lime chutney, a scattering of crispy fried onions and coriander leaves. Serve with the warm naan for scooping."
